&lt;P&gt;Well then I guess ALL my gear is meaningless.&amp;nbsp; SInce I rarely go below 90% mana (of 10k) even in RSS I guess I only need 1k mana and since I have 2k without any gear at all I guess I can go nekkid :smileyvery-happy:....Yeah right, whatever.&amp;nbsp; (joking btw)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The point is that in most &lt;U&gt;group&lt;/U&gt; situations you do not&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;EM&gt;&lt;U&gt;absolutely need&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;to med to full mana in order to continue XPing.&amp;nbsp; As I said, I will typically get to 30% and then med along the way using Yaulp and sitting when I can, and normally within ten minutes I am back to 90%+.&amp;nbsp; Anyone can do this you just have to be "mana efficient": use cheal whenever possible and use your other tools (DvA and epic 1.52.0&amp;nbsp;[if you have it], CR and EB) liberally.&amp;nbsp; If you don't have these other tools, then yes you probably do need to med up more than I do, but again, unless your group is sucking you dry, you should never&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;EM&gt;&lt;U&gt;have&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt; to med to full before continuing after a death.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Soloing is a different matter.&amp;nbsp; When I solo I never go below 50% mana (unless I die). When I hit 50% I know it's time to sit and med to full.&amp;nbsp; My reasoning is simple:&amp;nbsp; If I go to 0% mana and then med and a wandering mob walks in, the best I can do is run away.&amp;nbsp; If in this same situation I am at 50% mana I can and do take on that mob and then sit and med again.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
