      <title>Mana Pool Regeneration</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=9028#M9028</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Anyway, I think this deserves a thread of it's own. At any rate, especially at the high end with 9k+ pools the&amp;nbsp; downtime is rediculous. So here are my thoughts:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1. An aa that allows for sitting mana regeneration while sitting, or sharply increases the percentage per tick. Like increase mana regeneration 5%/10%/15% ect.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2. Raise med skill post 65.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3. Raise mana preservation from 20% to 25% and 30%.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4. Increase current FT cap post 65 to 20 innately, while allowing the AA to take it to 25. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;5. Reconfigure Meditation skill instead of a specific amount of mana regeneration per tick, it goes to&amp;nbsp; a percentile of mana per tick based on skill. This way the ability scales with mana pool.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
