      <title>Re: Mana Pool Regeneration</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=9048#M9048</link>
      <description>Slight derail here, but curiousity is getting the better of me from the previous poster's comments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Strictly by the numbers, Sitting regen is higher than Yaulp standing regen, all else being equal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In reality however, does this hold up? (Lets leave mounts out of the equation for the moment since they have their own issues)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you are yaulping, you are getting the Yaulp standing regen almost constantly; unless you sit down it is going 100% of the time (save for times when you have to swap spells, or have to quick heal enough that you can't squeeze a yaulp in between and it fades in that period). &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you are sitting/standing to cast, then depending on how you are healing, you may end up on your feet as often as you are sitting, in which case you are getting a total regen somewhere between sitting regen and standing regen without yaulp. Definitely less than sitting regen in any case, unless you can afford to stay seated the entire fight. Even if you are just CHealing, you are going to get 1 or 2 ticks of standing regen per cast no matter what. Even if you factor in mounts, you would be knocked to standing regen rates while casting; and I personally, only feel comfortable using mounts in a constant group where I know I can reliably heal and don't have to change my spell quickly.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I think what I'm trying to say here is the following:&lt;br&gt;In a fairly constant group (ie one with few pauses between mobs), does Yaulping throughout give you a better total mana regen rate than the sitting method?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;My gut feeling is that this does tend to be the case, but I'm not positive of it. I'm not even sure how to begin to work this sort of thing out concretely.</description>
